        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 11 at 10:40PM MDT by NWS Grand Junction CO</headline>
        <description>At 1039 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 16
miles southeast of Meeker, or 31 miles northwest of Glenwood Springs,
moving northeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Buford.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
